dcterms:description: The MIMIC-III dataset is a publicly available critical care database that contains de-identified health data associated with over 40,000 patients who stayed in critical care units at the Beth Israel Deaconess Medical Center. It includes various clinical events and physiological data, which can be used for health risk prediction tasks.
dcterms:title: MIMIC-III Dataset

dcterms:description: The End-stage Renal Disease (ESRD) dataset consists of records from patients who received therapy for end-stage renal disease in a real-world hospital setting. It includes clinical data and outcomes for patients over a specified period, used for mortality risk prediction.
dcterms:title: End-stage Renal Disease (ESRD) Dataset
